                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/21085: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-23T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 23, 1942—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>347. From the Under Secretary. Your 608, April 17, 6 p.m. You are assured that
                    the matters to which you refer are receiving immediate attention. [Welles.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
